node.text:
Nothing better than Mama Kwan in the house to watch some Olympics together! Can’t wait for the gymnastics (no spoilers please!!). 

1 lb tilapia (2 fillets) or cod/catfish
1 tablespoon of tajin (you can get this at most US supermarkets) 
1 tablespoon chili powder
1 teaspoon cumin
1 teaspoon cayenne pepper
½ teaspoon salt
½ teaspoon black pepper
1 tablespoon lime juice, about 1 lime
1 tablespoon olive oil

Side:
1 15 oz. black bean 
1 1/2 c. Frozen roasted corn (thawed) 
1/3 chopped cilantro 
1 clove of garlic minced 
1/2 red onion finely chopped
Jalapeño finely chopped (optional) 
1 tablespoon of olive oil 

Rinse and pat dry tilapia. Mix spices (cumin, tajin, chili powder, salt, pepper & cayenne) in a small bowl. Squeeze lime juice and coat tilapia then dust spices onto tilapia covering both sides of fish. Heat oil on medium heat and cook fish for 4-5 mins on both sides (depending on thickness). Set aside and keep warm. Using the same pan heat olive oil, toss in garlic, and onions and sauté for a minute. Add corn and beans and cook thorough for 2 mins until warm. Lightly fold in cilantro. 
Plate black bean/corn and then serve with tilapia. 

Enjoy!! And, Go USA 🇺🇸

node.text:
Repost @oniceperspectives 
•
After watching @the.skate.kid’s performance to Andra Day’s uplifting anthem on Black Lives Matter Plaza last June, and seeing her perform again on TV at yesterday’s inauguration, it became clear to me just how much the art of skating can and always has affected our national identity.
❄️
We filmed this on Christmas Day 2018 (hence the crowd!). MK has devoted her entire post-Olympic career to public service, first the U.S. Department of State, and then to the Clinton and Biden campaigns, as a public envoy for diplomacy and outreach. And it won’t stop there.
❄️
Thank you Kaitlyn Saunders (@the.skate.kid), Michelle Kwan, Andra Day and the millions of hearts and artists out there who made yesterday possible. Let’s keep rising up, and fighting for a better, more diverse, tolerant, and inclusive future, for our sport and our world. __⛸
❄️
__🎥 Jordan @oniceperspectives
__⛸ @michellewkwan
__👣 Choreo @karenwkwan
__🎵 Rise Up @andraday
__📍 @iceatsantamonica @dtsantamonica 
__🗓 December 25, 2018

node.text: So proud of this champion @allysonfelix! You showed us how to win with character and humility. Congrats on making history and winning your 10th Olympic medal🏅 and first as a mom! You’re an incredible role model both on and off the track.

node.text: I can’t get enough of the Olympic coverage - brings back all the feels and emotions. This photo captured so much for me that my heart is about to burst. I came home after winning the Olympic festival (where Olympic hopefuls compete) and showed my grandparents my gold medal at my family’s Chinese restaurant. They were beaming with pride and, even though they spoke no English, they showed off the medal to every customer that walked in. My parents & grandparents had worked so hard to make sure that I had the opportunity to do what I loved and I am forever grateful for their sacrifices. I was clearly living the American Dream 🤩

Nothing better than Mama Kwan in the house to watch some Olympics together! Can’t wait for the gymnastics (no spoilers please!!). 

1 lb tilapia (2 fillets) or cod/catfish
1 tablespoon of tajin (you can get this at most US supermarkets) 
1 tablespoon chili powder
1 teaspoon cumin
1 teaspoon cayenne pepper
½ teaspoon salt
½ teaspoon black pepper
1 tablespoon lime juice, about 1 lime
1 tablespoon olive oil

Side:
1 15 oz. black bean 
1 1/2 c. Frozen roasted corn (thawed) 
1/3 chopped cilantro 
1 clove of garlic minced 
1/2 red onion finely chopped
Jalapeño finely chopped (optional) 
1 tablespoon of olive oil 

Rinse and pat dry tilapia. Mix spices (cumin, tajin, chili powder, salt, pepper & cayenne) in a small bowl. Squeeze lime juice and coat tilapia then dust spices onto tilapia covering both sides of fish. Heat oil on medium heat and cook fish for 4-5 mins on both sides (depending on thickness). Set aside and keep warm. Using the same pan heat olive oil, toss in garlic, and onions and sauté for a minute. Add corn and beans and cook thorough for 2 mins until warm. Lightly fold in cilantro. 
Plate black bean/corn and then serve with tilapia. 

Enjoy!! And, Go USA 🇺🇸
